Description: Wheat Farming - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in growing wheat and/or producing wheat seeds.
Dairy Cattle and Milk Production - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in milking dairy cattle.
Timber Tract Operations - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the operation of timber tracts for the purpose of selling standing timber.
Hunting and Trapping - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in commercial hunting and trapping.

Support Activities for Forestry - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in performing support activities related to timber production, wood technology, forestry economics, and forest protection.
Natural Gas Extraction - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the exploration, development, and production of natural gas.
Water Supply and Irrigation Systems - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in operating water treatment plants and water supply systems.

Commercial and Institutional Building Construction - This industry comprises establishments primarily responsible for the construction (including new work, additions, alterations, maintenance, and repairs) of commercial and institutional buildings.

Highway, Street, and Bridge Construction - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the construction of highways (including elevated), streets, roads, airport runways, public sidewalks, or bridges.
Electrical Contractors and Other Wiring Installation Contractors - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in installing and servicing electrical wiring and equipment.
Fluid Milk Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing fluid milk and cream from raw milk and/or processed milk products.
Breweries - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in brewing beer, ale, malt liquors, and nonalcoholic beer.
Fiber, Yarn, and Thread Mills - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in spinning yarn from fibers and/or manufacturing thread of any fiber.
Textile Bag and Canvas Mills - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing textile bags or canvases.
Cut and Sew Apparel Contractors - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing cut and sew apparel.
Sawmills - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in sawing dimension lumber, boards, beams, timbers, poles, ties, shingles, shakes, siding, and wood chips from logs and bolts.
Paper (except Newsprint) Mills - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing paper (except newsprint) and paperboard.
Commercial Printing (except Screen and Books) - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in commercial printing (except screen and books).
Petroleum Refineries - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in refining crude petroleum into refined petroleum.
Industrial Gas Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing industrial organic and inorganic gases.
Plastics Material and Resin Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing plastics materials and resins.
Ready-Mix Concrete Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing ready-mix concrete and delivering it to purchasers in a plastic and unhardened state.
Iron and Steel Mills and Ferroalloy Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing iron and steel and/or alloys.
Machine Shops - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in machining precision turned products or precision machining parts.
Construction Machinery Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing construction machinery.
Electronic Computer Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing and/or assembling electronic computers.
Residential Electric Lighting Fixture Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing residential electric lighting fixtures.
Heavy Duty Truck Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing heavy-duty trucks.
Wood Kitchen Cabinet and Countertop Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing wood or non-wood kitchen cabinets and countertops.
Surgical and Medical Instrument Manufacturing - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in manufacturing medical instruments and devices.
Automobile and Other Motor Vehicle Merchant Wholesalers - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the merchant wholesale distribution of motor vehicles.
Drugs and Druggists' Sundries Merchant Wholesalers - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the merchant wholesale distribution of drugs and druggists' sundries.
Business to Business Electronic Markets - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in bringing together buyers and sellers of goods using the internet or other electronic means.
New Car Dealers - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing new automobiles and light trucks.
Furniture Stores - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing new furniture.
Home Centers - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing a general line of home repair and improvement materials.
Supermarkets and Other Grocery (except Convenience) Stores - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing a general line of food products.
Pharmacies and Drug Stores - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing prescription or nonprescription drugs and medicines.

Gasoline Stations with Convenience Stores - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing automotive fuels (e.g., gasoline, diesel fuel) in combination with convenience store or food mart items.
Men's Clothing Stores - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing a general line of men's and boys' clothing.
Sporting Goods Stores - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing new sporting goods.
Department Stores - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing a wide range of merchandise, typically organized into departments.
Florists - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing cut flowers, potted plants, and floral arrangements.
Mail-Order Houses - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in retailing all types of merchandise using mail catalogs or television programs.
Scheduled Passenger Air Transportation - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing air transportation of passengers.
Line-Haul Railroads - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing rail transportation of passengers and/or cargo using railroad rolling stock.
Deep Sea, Coastal, and Great Lakes Water Transportation - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing deep sea, coastal, and Great Lakes water transportation of cargo.
General Freight Trucking, Local - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing local general freight trucking.
Urban Transit Systems - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in operating local and suburban passenger transit systems over regular routes and on regular schedules.
Pipeline Transportation of Crude Oil - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the pipeline transportation of crude oil.
Other Airport Operations - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing airport operations and related services, excluding air traffic control.
Couriers and Express Delivery Services - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing courier and express delivery services.
General Warehousing and Storage - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in operating warehousing and storage facilities for general merchandise.
Periodical Publishers - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in publishing periodicals, including magazines and journals.
Motion Picture and Video Production - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in producing motion pictures, videos, television programs, or commercials.
Television Broadcasting - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in broadcasting visual programs by television to the public, except cable and subscription programming.
Wired Telecommunications Carriers - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing wired telecommunications services.
Data Processing, Hosting, and Related Services - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing infrastructure for hosting or data processing services.
Commercial Banking - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in accepting deposits and making commercial loans.
Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in underwriting health and medical insurance policies.
Lessors of Nonresidential Buildings (except Miniwarehouses) - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in acting as lessors of nonresidential buildings.
Offices of Lawyers - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the practice of law.
Offices of Other Holding Companies - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in holding securities of companies other than banks.
Temporary Help Services - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in supplying temporary workers to clients.
Colleges, Universities, and Professional Schools - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing academic courses and granting degrees.
Offices of Physicians (except Mental Health Specialists) - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the private or group practice of general or specialized medicine or surgery.
Nursing Care Facilities (Skilled Nursing Facilities) - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing inpatient nursing and rehabilitative services.
Theater Companies and Dinner Theaters - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in producing live theatrical presentations.
Amusement and Theme Parks - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in operating amusement parks and theme parks.
Hotels (except Casino Hotels) and Motels - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing short-term lodging in facilities known as hotels, motor hotels, and motels.
Full-Service Restaurants - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing food services to patrons who order and are served while seated.
General Automotive Repair - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing automotive repair and maintenance services.
Beauty Salons - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in providing beauty services such as hair care, nail care, and skin care.
Religious Organizations - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in operating religious organizations.
Legislative Bodies - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in legislative activities.
Courts - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in administering justice.
Administration of Education Programs - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the administration of education programs.

Administration of Air and Water Resource and Solid Waste Management Programs - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the administration of air and water resource and solid waste management programs.
Administration of Housing Programs - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the administration of housing programs.
Administration of General Economic Programs - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in the administration of general economic programs.
Space Research and Technology - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in conducting space research and technology development.
National Security - This industry comprises establishments primarily engaged in national security activities.
